cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL 

The paper discusses a new data analytics framework that separates computation from intermediate data, which is a key aspect of database systems. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions experiments with batch, streaming, and graph analytics workloads, which are common in distributed computing and data structures, making cs.DC and cs.DS likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses programmable monitoring and event abstraction, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
